# Row action button colors

Use shared styling from `app/ui/row_action_colors.py` (`inject_row_action_colors_css`, called via `inject_global_css`).

## Color map

| Action | Style | Key suffix examples |
|--------|--------|---------------------|
| Open / View | Blue bg, white icon | `_open_`, `_view_` |
| Edit | White/outline neutral | `_more_edit_`, `_det_edit_`, `estimates_modal_edit_`, `_tool_edit_` |
| Move / Reclassify | Blue | `_trailer_go_`, `_ctype_`, `_row_move_`, `_reclass_` |
| Delete | Red (trash icon) | `_del_`, `_delete_` — styled in `inject_action_colors_css` |
| Cancel | White/outline neutral | `_confirm_cancel_`, `est_cancel_new`, `job_cancel_new` |

## Button keys

Use `row_action_key(prefix, action, record_id)` or `{prefix}_{action}_{id}` so CSS can target `st-key-*` classes.

```python
# Good — picked up by shared CSS
st.button("↗", key=f"ast_open_{aid}", help="Open asset details")
st.button("Edit", key=f"inv_more_edit_{iid}", use_container_width=True)

# Avoid — generic keys won't get semantic colors
st.button("↗", key=f"btn_{aid}")
```

## Rules

- Row Open/View: compact `↗` icon on one horizontal row; do not stack.
- Popover menus (`⋯`): text labels OK; inline row icons follow the color map.
- Scope page-specific sizing in page CSS; colors stay in `row_action_colors.py`.
